description: In the Sagittarius sector, a new planet is being populated with clones and will be transformed into an agricultural planet. We are watching Ustin being manipulated into the worker-religion. In the same time, Stin, the other clone with the same genetic material will face similar problems due to the envy and pride of clone Jeremiah. By the end, we see the imminent attack of a barbarian horde.
name: Trufia si invidia sunt pacate de moarte

description:
The Abbey's walls are to be attacked by a barbarian horde. Rim is asked by the Abbot to lead the monks into battle. Rim's army is outnumbered and not really prepared to fight.

This issue also includes a short story called Aldebaraan, credited to Alexandru Popa, which shows the way the Quints are being trained.

description:
Reprints material from Doctor Who: Four Doctors #1, #2 and #3.

This brand-new issue features strip from the 'Doctor Who: Four Doctors' crossover event series - featuring the first ever meeting of the Tenth, Eleventh and Twelfth Doctors!

Part 1

What shocking past event brings three Doctors together – to combat an unknown foe with three incarnations in its sights?

Part 2

The three Doctors meet in 1920s Paris – impossible! Have the laws of time and space been broken?

Part 3

Into the lion's den! The Doctors take the fight to the enemy... but have they already been outmanoeuvred?
name: Four Doctors

description: Jubei disobeyed the orders of his master — thus he must die. The young Tetsuo is entrusted with the task to find him and bring him to his fate. Along the way, though, an unexpected revelation will change the course of his mission…

description: On the background of mid-XIX century colonial India, the love story between Elisabeth and Jim risks to be trounced by the rebellion climate increasingly spreading in the country… but there's more: the threat of an unwanted third party looms over them. Willing to marry the girl, this man won't be shy to plan a cunning murderous scheme...
name: La Rivolta dei Sepoy

description:
Sometimes in the supplements published by Edifumetto, there weren't the same characters of the regular series.

This is one of those cases, and this is a parody of the famous comic "Tim Tyler's luck" ("Cino & Franco" in Italy), published around the '30s.
name: I due avventurieri

description:
Strangely enough in the supplements published by Edifumetto, sometimes there weren't the same characters of the regular series. This is one of those cases.

The series Necron had been closed in 1981, due to poor sales and to the continuing delay in the delivery of the drawings by Magnus. So for tax reasons, in September 1983, what should have been #12 of the volume "Necron" comes out, instead, as a supplement to Zora nuova serie #44.
name: NECRON - Sopraffatta dai mostri

description:
76-Pages of Astounding Action-Packed Arachnid-Adventure! £3.50!

Spider-Verse continues!

The first huge battle! But if the first fights were just skirmishes this can’t be good for the Spider-Army. Miles Morales shows his stuff! Silk finds something valuable on her run and meet the most suprising Spider-Character yet!

Plus, Kaine, Ben Reilly and Ultimate Black Widow discover what horrors lurk inside Jennix’s lab!

Also, Silk is pursued by the Inheritor twins, Brix and Bora! Meanwhile, Spider-Woman goes on a secret mission that takes her into the very heart of darkness… Loomworld!

By Mike, Costa, Paco Diaz, Dennis Hopeless, Greg Land, Dan Slott and Giuseppe Camuncoli,!

Includes material reprinted from Scarlet Spiders #2, Spider-Woman #2, and Amazing Spider-Man Vol.4 #12!

Spider-Man 2099 and Lady Spider capture Daemos! But how long can they hold him?!

Plus, Kaine, Ben Reilly and Ultimate Black Widow versus the merciless might of Jennix!

By Peter David, Will Sliney, Mike, Costa, Paco Diaz, Dennis Hopeless and Greg Land!
